content: River in Singapore **Sungei Tampines** ([IPA](/wiki/International_Phonetic_Alphabet): /ˈsʊŋaɪ ˈtæmpəniːs/, [Malay](/wiki/Malay_language) for *Tampines River*) is a river in [Pasir Ris](/wiki/Pasir_Ris), [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore). It is named for a type of tree that reportedly grew in the area, *[Streblus elongatus](/wiki/Streblus_elongatus)*, commonly known as "tempinis" in Malay. 1°22′54″N 103°57′15″E﻿ / ﻿1.3817°N 103.9542°E﻿ / 1.3817; 103.9542 This [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) location article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. - v - t - e
title: Sungei Tampines
